cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV 

This paper is about named entity recognition (NER) using a bidirectional LSTM (long short term memory) encoder with a neural conditional random fields (CRF) decoder (biLSTM-CRF). The paper discusses several methods to optimize the performance of networks based on this architecture, which are related to exploration of parameter space, regularization of LSTMs, and penalization of confident output distributions. These topics are relevant to several sub-categories of computer science, including natural language processing (cs.CL), machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI), neural networks (cs.NE), and computer vision (cs.CV). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL, followed by cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, and cs.CV.
